Here is a few tests you can run to see how it works (this assumes you ssh to 10.16.132.165 with root / smartvm )

evmcmd managementsystem_listall
evmcmd managementsystem_gettags emsGuid=02f0f85e-3b54-11e3-bce6-005056b367d4
evmcmd managementsystem_settags emsGuid=02f0f85e-3b54-11e3-bce6-005056b367d4 category=department name=accounting
evmcmd managementsystem_details emsGuid=02f0f85e-3b54-11e3-bce6-005056b367d4
evmcmd cluster_listall
evmcmd host_listall
evmcmd host_gettags hostGuid=29344dcc-3b54-11e3-97a2-005056b367d4
evmcmd host_gettags hostGuid=28838a46-3b54-11e3-97a2-005056b367d4
evmcmd virtualmachine_listall
evmcmd virtualmachine_gettags vmGuid=2a4765fa-3b54-11e3-97a2-005056b367d4
evmcmd virtualmachine_details vmGuid=2a4765fa-3b54-11e3-97a2-005056b367d4
evmcmd cluster_listall
evmcmd resourcepool_listall
evmcmd datastore_listall
evmcmd ems_version

Or alternatively by running the evmcmd itself to bring up the prompt to the run the same tests above but without evmcmd
